channel.description: A feed of recent tweets from gutenbergtimes.

item.description: Gutenberg Changelog #68 - WordCamp Europe, Gutenberg 13.4 and WordPress 6.1 - co-hosts Mary Job @maryojob + Birgit Pauli-Haack @bph discuss with Dave Smith @get_dave the latest release, what's to come in WordPres 6.1 and so much more https://t.co/FkhAWKAbwh

Block First Approach, Gutenberg 13.4, Page vs Site Editor - Weekend Edition 218 with contributions among others by @jeffikus @m_munirkamal @GeorginaReeder @nickmdiego @get_dave @martinibuster @matias_ventura https://t.co/ugN2uoJnn7
Matias Ventura couldn't make it to Saturday's keynote. He prepared a few cool things, he wanted to show now in this thread. :-) https://t.co/S8E5EOuzi8

WordCamp Europe + Roadmap 6.1 Edition 217 with #WCEU lightning talks by @SeanBlakeley @juanmaguitar @ryanwelcher @imranhsayed @circlecube @paulfhalfpenny and talks by @gziolo @nerrad @iamposti More Gutenberg updates by @matias_ventura @get_dave @wpbuilds https://t.co/4MJN9Ljtmo

The Museum of Block Art is now offering an official way to submit your art. Explore the power of the editor, create something wonderful, and give back to the community all at once. https://t.co/UGP3rvhkNm
